#: ../../../internals/layout_in_calldata.rst:6
msgid "Layout of Call Data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/layout_in_calldata.rst:8
msgid ""
"The input data for a function call is assumed to be in the format defined by "
"the :ref:`ABI specification <ABI>`. Among others, the ABI specification "
"requires arguments to be padded to multiples of 32 bytes. The internal "
"function calls use a different convention."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../internals/layout_in_calldata.rst:12
msgid ""
"Arguments for the constructor of a contract are directly appended at the end "
"of the contract's code, also in ABI encoding. The constructor will access "
"them through a hard-coded offset, and not by using the ``codesize`` opcode, "
"since this of course changes when appending data to the code."
msgstr ""
